I was in the EC tunnel as my 30th level bard Lanow,and someone named Brittan(she has another character named Viower or Viowers if anyone wants to know)wanted to see my armor. She made it sound like she was going to offer me a lot of money for it. I put all of my gear in the trade window, and my singing steel and wakizashi of the frozen skies in a bag so it would all fit. She /Qed out, but I thought she just went linkdead. She came back and told what order to arrange the items in in the trade window. I thought she just wanted to make sure it would all fit in her inventory so it would all go in the correct bags. Then she /Qed out again, the bag with my singing steel fell to the ground and her other character picked it up and ran away. I talked to a GM about it and he was useless. Later that day I talked to a wizard who said the same thing happened to him, and the same person scammed him. I ended up losing my armor and weapons that I spent 30 levels working to get. If you don't want this to happen to you, then when trading, do not put bags and loose items in the trade window together, if the loose items go in a main slot instead of another bag then there will be no room for the bags. When someone just cancels a trade then any items that there aren't room for will go on your cursor, if the person goes linkdead though, the items will go the ground. Oh well, I don't think I am going to play my bard much anymore, nothing to look forward to when you lose all of your good armor and weapons, I'll have to play my 12th level SK, Torklin then.

